name: BUNK'D
overview: Siblings Emma, Ravi, and Zuri Ross leave their extravagant New York City penthouse once again to return to Camp Kikiwaka, a rustic summer camp in Maine where their parents met as teenagers.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The Ross kids leave their extravagant New York City penthouse and head off to Camp Kikiwaka. Together Emma, Ravi and Zuri must navigate the hijinks and curveballs thrown by the owner of the camp, Gladys, who with the help of her sneaky niece Hazel, is out to get them because of her decades-old rivalry with their mom.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Emma and Ravi resume their role as CIT’s bringing with them the experiences from their first summer at camp. Together with Zuri, her best friend and bunk-mate Tiffany, the cheerful head counselor Lou, the camp heartthrob Xander, and the hilariously imaginative Jorge, the campers embark on new and exciting adventures during their stay at Camp Kikiwaka. The friends welcome an unexpected camper with a dubious past named Griff, Xander gets to showcase his musical talents, familiar faces return for a visit and special friendships are formed and solidified, all the while overcoming unforeseen encounters that arise.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Returning to camp, the campers find some changes around them.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: After purchasing Camp Kikiwaka—for one dollar—from the Ross siblings, the always cheerful Lou is adjusting to her new duties as camp director with her usual brand of over-the-top enthusiasm. She’s thrilled to be reunited with campers Destiny, Finn and Matteo, who have returned for another exciting summer full of fun and friendship. Lou also welcomes some new faces, including camp counselor Noah, an upbeat and enthusiastic actor from Hollywood; Ava, a tenacious counselor from the big city; and Gwen, an eccentric new camper who has spent her entire life living off the grid.

seasons.name: Season 5
seasons.overview: Back for another exciting summer at the sometimes struggling Camp Kikiwaka in rural Maine are the enthusiastic camp owner/director Lou, counselors Ava and Noah, and returning campers Destiny, Matteo and Finn, who are all ready to tackle new and hilarious adventures.

seasons.name: Leaning the Ropes
seasons.overview: Lou, Parker, Destiny and Noah arrive at the soon-to-be Kikiwaka Ranch in Dusty Tush, Wyoming, where Lou must convince the surly owner, a.k.a. "The Marshal" to officially sell the property to her. In the meantime, counselors Noah and Destiny have their hands full with the newly arrived campers, including Bill, a no-nonsense descendant of famous cowboy Bill Pickett who prefers roping cattle to hanging out with friends; Winnie, a fearless girl who's earned the nickname "Wild Winnie" by breaking the rules and occasionally blowing things up; and Jake, a laid-back, easy-going boy who also happens to be a video-gaming fanatic.

seasons.name: Leaning the Ropes
seasons.overview: The hijinks continue at Kikiwaka Ranch with Lou, her right-hand man Parker, plus counselors Destiny and Noah along for the ride. Cowboy Bill, daredevil Winnie and gamer Jake are also back for another summer full of excitement and new adventures.

episodes.name: Welcome to Camp Kikiwaka
episodes.overview: In the premiere episode, the Ross kids arrive at camp. The camp's owner, Gladys, is even scarier than the legendary creature that's rumored to stalk the grounds. With the help of her sneaky niece Hazel, she's out to get the Ross kids because of her decades-old rivalry with their mom.

episodes.name: Gone Girl
episodes.overview: Ravi becomes suspicious when he overhears Xander’s plans for his first date with Emma. Meanwhile, Zuri and Jorge set up a secret business selling candy and video games to the campers.

episodes.name: Camp Rules
episodes.overview: Emma and Zuri won’t stop fighting, so Lou sends them out in a canoe in the middle of the lake to work out their differences.

episodes.name: Smells Like Camp Spirit
episodes.overview: Emma and Xander lose the camp spirit stick, which curses the campers with bad luck! Meanwhile, Jorge and Tiffany try to teach Ravi how to swim.

episodes.name: The Ones That Got Away
episodes.overview: Emma and Xander team up for a fishing competition. Meanwhile, Zuri and Tiffany devise a plan to steal fish from the mess hall to submit in the contest.

episodes.name: Can You Hear Me Now?
episodes.overview: Zuri secretly keeps her cell phone beyond the allotted time, which puts Emma in a tough spot. Meanwhile, Ravi and Tiffany are duped into making a cell phone tower that is hidden in the new camp totem pole.

episodes.name: Friending with the Enemy
episodes.overview: Emma convinces Lou that they should make an effort to become friends with Hazel. Meanwhile, a TV producer gets Ravi, Zuri and Tiffany to help him hunt the legendary Kikiwaka monster.

episodes.name: Waka, Waka, Waka!
episodes.overview: Ravi and Tiffany get video proof that the Kikiwaka exists. Meanwhile, Emma and Lou try to outsell Hazel at the Kikiwaka Day Festival.

episodes.name: Secret Santa
episodes.overview: Emma and Lou are determined to hold a holiday gift exchange, but when Ravi gives them advice, it doesn’t quite work out as planned. When Zuri, Xander, Jorge, and Tiffany run into a man they think is the real Santa, they need to work together to cheer him up and save Christmas.

episodes.name: Counselors' Night Off
episodes.overview: Emma sneaks out to the "Counselors' Night Out" party to eavesdrop on Xander, leaving Ravi in charge back at camp.

episodes.name: There's No Place Like Camp
episodes.overview: When Xander and Ravi realize that Jorge is homesick, they enlist the help of Emma, Zuri and Tiffany to cheer him up.

episodes.name: Luke's Back
episodes.overview: Luke reunites with his siblings to get some summer school help from Ravi. Meanwhile a turf war erupts between Camp Kikiwaka and the rival camp across the lake.

episodes.name: No Escape
episodes.overview: When Jorge and Zuri sneak out to buy something from the general store in town, Emma and Xander have to get them back before Gladys notices they’re all gone!

episodes.name: Close Encounters of the Camp Kind
episodes.overview: After the campers think they see a UFO land in Lake Kikiwaka, a new boy shows up and Jorge and Tiffany think he's an alien. Meanwhile, Emma and Ravi get evaluated by the camp counselors.

episodes.name: Crafted and Shafted
episodes.overview: During an overnight camping trip, the kids must use their survival skills after Emma and Xander get lost in a cave.

episodes.name: Boo Boos and Birthdays
episodes.overview: Emma and Zuri butt heads when trying to plan a surprise birthday party for Tiffany. Meanwhile, in order to get out of a volleyball tournament, Ravi and Jorge fake injuries.

episodes.name: For Love and Money
episodes.overview: Lou falls for a handsome young lumberjack, but Emma and Zuri are suspicious of him. Xander sets Ravi and Jorge on a treasure hunt.

episodes.name: Love Is for the Birds
episodes.overview: Emma and Jorge help Ravi when he starts dating a girl who is his polar opposite. Meanwhile, Zuri and Tiffany try to return an eagle egg to its nest.

episodes.name: Bride and Doom
episodes.overview: The campers learn about Olga, the daughter of the camp founder whose ghost supposedly haunts Kikiwaka. A camp wedding may be the only way to rid the camp of the ghost.

episodes.name: Live from Camp Kikiwaka
episodes.overview: When Gladys announces that Camp Kikiwaka may close, Emma, Xander and Lou host a live stream to try and save the camp.

episodes.name: Xander Says Goodbye
episodes.overview: Emma and Xander are forced to make some tough decisions when his dad wants him to leave camp for football training. Meanwhile, Emma, Ravi and Lou put him through some drills.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: The Ross kids leave their extravagant New York City penthouse and head off to Camp Kikiwaka. Together Emma, Ravi and Zuri must navigate the hijinks and curveballs thrown by the owner of the camp, Gladys, who with the help of her sneaky niece Hazel, is out to get them because of her decades-old rivalry with their mom.

episodes.name: Griff Is in the House!
episodes.overview: The Ross kids leave their New York penthouse and return to Camp Kikiwaka for the summer where to their surprise, find an unexpected camp addition and the Woodchuck cabin’s new startling counselor.

episodes.name: Dance in My Pants
episodes.overview: Camp Kikiwaka hosts its annual dance which has Tiffany and Zuri hopeful that they’ll dance with a cute boy. Emma learns that Lou and Xander have a history.

episodes.name: Zuri Has a Little Lamb
episodes.overview: Lou assigns Zuri and Emma to barn duty. Meanwhile, the boys discover that Gladys has been hiding a secret in the woods.

episodes.name: Weasel Out
episodes.overview: To Zuri's dismay, Hazel makes her a CIT in the Weasel cabin. Jorge and Griff convince Ravi that the camp's horse has a hidden talent.

episodes.name: Queen of Screams
episodes.overview: Jorge enters a short story contest and wins a dinner with his favorite horror novelist, Stephanie Queen, and decides to bring along a few of his fellow campers for the thrilling experience. Meanwhile, Xander must act as referee between Emma and Ravi.

episodes.name: Luke Out Below
episodes.overview: Luke returns to camp and decides to take Griff and Zuri on an adventure to prove that he can be just as responsible as the other CITs.

episodes.name: Camp Kiki-Slasher
episodes.overview: Things get scary at Camp Kikiwaka when the campers start disappearing one by one. When they finally uncover the culprit with the axe to grind, he takes them on a thrill ride the campers will never forget!

episodes.name: Treehouse of Terror
episodes.overview: Zuri, Jorge and Tiffany enlist the support of an unexpected camper to help restore an abandoned tree house they found as their new hangout. Meanwhile, Emma and Lou, Ravi and Xander get competitive during a friendly game of billiards.

episodes.name: Tidal Wave
episodes.overview: Zuri helps Xander create a music video for his song "Tidal Wave" in the hopes of turning him into a social media star; meanwhile, Ravi and Lou join forces to try to do something nice for Griff.

episodes.name: Fog'd In
episodes.overview: A strange, toxic fog overtakes Camp Kikiwaka causing the campers to develop bizarrely altered personalities and it’s up to the camp counselors to save the day.

episodes.name: How the Griff Stole Christmas
episodes.overview: The campers participate in a gift-making activity for the upcoming holiday and Griff is not into it. Ravi and Lou try to create a special memory for Griff, while Santa asks Jorge to babysit for one of his reindeers.

episodes.name: Food Fight
episodes.overview: When Murphy challenges the kids to cook the camp dinner, Zuri orchestrates a heated competition between the counselors and the CITs.

episodes.name: Mother May I?
episodes.overview: Lou is in awe when her hero, the legendary Christina Ross, pays a visit to Camp Kikiwaka. The boys from Grizzly Cabin head out for an overnight camping trip.

episodes.name: Mud Fight
episodes.overview: After disobeying Ravi's wishes when on a hike, Zuri, Tiffany and Jorge get into a muddy situation. Meanwhile, Lou finds herself smitten and imagines what her life would be like in 1916 with her crush.

episodes.name: Dog Days of Summer
episodes.overview: When Lou decides to leave Camp Kikiwaka after she learns about the passing of her dog, the campers get together to help her realize how much she means to them.

episodes.name: Bad Dog!
episodes.overview: Emma, Tiffany and Zuri are not happy when Lou's new puppy, Chuck, wreaks havoc on the Woodchuck cabin. Meanwhile, Ravi encourages Jorge to do his best to set a camp record in order receive a plaque.

episodes.name: Camp Stinky Waka
episodes.overview: When Tiffany’s mother comes to visit, the Woodchucks try to help Tiffany pretend that Camp Kikiwaka is a camp for geniuses.

episodes.name: Cabin vs. Cabin
episodes.overview: The Woodchuck, Grizzly and Weasel cabins compete in Camp Kikiwaka's annual "Cabin of the Year” competition.

episodes.name: Dreams Come True
episodes.overview: As the end of camp nears, Griff gets some unexpected news that changes his life.

episodes.name: We Didn't Start the Fire
episodes.overview: To celebrate their last night at camp, the kids go on an overnight camping trip; Ravi and Emma take their final tests to become counselors.

episodes.name: The Great Escape
episodes.overview: Xander and Emma learn two of their campers have a crush on one another.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Emma and Ravi resume their role as CIT’s bringing with them the experiences from their first summer at camp. Together with Zuri, her best friend and bunk-mate Tiffany, the cheerful head counselor Lou, the camp heartthrob Xander, and the hilariously imaginative Jorge, the campers embark on new and exciting adventures during their stay at Camp Kikiwaka. The friends welcome an unexpected camper with a dubious past named Griff, Xander gets to showcase his musical talents, familiar faces return for a visit and special friendships are formed and solidified, all the while overcoming unforeseen encounters that arise.

episodes.name: We Can't Bear It!
episodes.overview: Returning to camp, the campers find some changes around them.

episodes.name: Let's Bounce!
episodes.overview: After learning they are officially the new owners of Camp Kikiwaka, the Ross siblings have to decide which one of them will actually be in charge of the camp.

episodes.name: Take the Cake
episodes.overview: When Lou decides that the campers should practice public speaking, Matteo and Destiny help Finn overcome his fear.

episodes.name: O Sister, Where Art Thou?
episodes.overview: Ravi helps Matteo overcome his fears using hypnosis, but Matteo's newfound confidence could get him into trouble.

episodes.name: Cav'd In
episodes.overview: After Matteo and Finn express their frustration with Ravi's spying, Ravi decides to use a drone to spy on them instead.

episodes.name: By All Memes
episodes.overview: Emma decides to give everyone back their cell phones to foster camp unity and bring everyone closer together on her new Campstagram app.

episodes.name: A Whole Lotta Lobsta
episodes.overview: The Kikiwaka lobster festival is coming up and the Ross kids are determined to make it the best festival ever. Unfortunately, everything goes wrong and it ends up being a disaster!

episodes.name: No Bones About It
episodes.overview: Matteo and Finn come across a strange collection of bones and suspect the bones are from a new species. They set a trap for the creature and want credit for their new discovery.

episodes.name: Finder's Keepers, Lou's a Weeper
episodes.overview: Finn, Matteo, and Destiny fix up an old car as a present for Lou's 10-year anniversary at Camp Kikiwaka. Emma, Ravi, and Zuri decide to throw Lou a surprise party.

episodes.name: Reversal of Fortune
episodes.overview: The counselors clean out the storage room and find a fortuneteller machine that reveals something important will go missing and a sister will betray another sister.

episodes.name: Gruel and Unusual Punishment
episodes.overview: The children explore the booths at Camp Kikiwaka's Olde Moose Rump Days; after finding an old wooden box from Zuri's booth, the kids suddenly find themselves in the 1600s wearing Colonial garb.

episodes.name: Up, Up and Away
episodes.overview: Because Emma, Zuri and Ravi have new jobs, their mother wants to sell the camp. Worried that Lou will be devastated when she finds out, the three tell it her on a balloon ride.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: Returning to camp, the campers find some changes around them.

episodes.name: Who da Boss? Lou da Boss!
episodes.overview: It’s a new summer at Camp Kikiwaka as Lou takes over as camp director and welcomes new camper Gwen and camp counselors Noah and Ava.

episodes.name: Kikiwaka's Got Talent
episodes.overview: Finn and Matteo’s friendship is tested as they try to figure out an act for Camp Kikiwaka’s annual talent show. Meanwhile, Destiny tries to impress Noah with her pageant skills.

episodes.name: Yes, Lies and Tower Escape
episodes.overview: After Gwen accidentally breaks a window, she and Destiny get caught in a web of lies. Noah challenges Ava to be open to more things by saying “yes and …” to opportunities.

episodes.name: An Udder Disaster
episodes.overview: Finn offers to care for Lou’s beloved cow Bessie but must prove he can handle the responsibility. Meanwhile, Destiny and Gwen concoct a plan to patch things up between Ava and her mother, and Matteo helps Noah learn French for an audition.

episodes.name: Hot Spring Friend Machine
episodes.overview: Lou helps Gwen build her confidence when she learns that her parents plan to send her to school at the end of the summer. Ava discovers a hot spring at Camp Kikiwaka and enlists Noah to keep it a secret.

episodes.name: Water Under the Dock
episodes.overview: Destiny organizes a square dance to raise money to clean up Lake Kikiwaka and invites Noah’s arch-acting rival, Austin Justin. Meanwhile, Lou and Finn offer Matteo advice after learning he wants to ask Gwen to dance.

episodes.name: In Your Wildest Screams
episodes.overview: Gwen warns everyone that her dream effigy doll, Cuddles, can cause nightmares. The others laugh, but it doesn’t take long to realize Cuddles’ true power.

episodes.name: Inn Trouble
episodes.overview: Camp Kikiwaka gets a surprise visitor … Hazel! Hazel says she’s changed, so Lou agrees to let her hang out for a few days. The boys attempt to earn the camp’s highest honor.

episodes.name: Lake Rancid
episodes.overview: When a magazine contacts Destiny to do a story on her community service, Matteo, Gwen and Finn help her clean only one area of the shore, hiding the rest of the trash.

episodes.name: Between a Raccoon and a Hard Place
episodes.overview: Gwen befriends the Extreme Team, a group of campers known for its gutsy outdoor activities and accepts an invitation to hike to Dead Horse Drop.

episodes.name: Mo-Squito Mo Problems
episodes.overview: Mosquitoes are rampant, so Matteo looks to science to create a repellent. However, he ends up taking credit for something that Gwen invented.

episodes.name: Sore Lou-ser
episodes.overview: It’s time for the annual “Sportsmanship Games” against Kikiwaka’s rival, Camp Champion. Lou tries her best to “coach up” the campers knowing that Kikiwaka loses every year.

episodes.name: Lone Wolf
episodes.overview: Gwen is surprised when her older brother Jasper unexpectedly shows up to Camp Kikiwaka and encourages her to leave with him.

episodes.name: Serfs Up-rising
episodes.overview: It’s Renaissance week, so Lou assigns roles for each camper to play. Finn is declared the king and gets to run the camp for a week, but he ultimately makes the camp miserable.

episodes.name: Summer Winter Wonderland
episodes.overview: When the temperature drops, Lou deems it Christmas in July; Gwen reveals that she doesn't understand Christmas traditions, so Lou shows her what real Christmas spirit is all about.

episodes.name: Cramped Champions
episodes.overview: The pool at Camp Champion floods the grounds. Barb and her campers are left camp-less. Lou invites Barb and her kids to stay at Kikiwaka for a week, but immediately regrets it.

episodes.name: A Tale of Two Stackers
episodes.overview: When Lou discovers the diary of the camp founder, Jedediah Swearengen, she is shocked to learn that her hero was a traitor! It’s up to Destiny and Ava to snap Lou out of her funk.

episodes.name: Whatever Floats Your Goat Boat
episodes.overview: Lou discovers that Mayor Higgins, who is up for re-election, is actually a goat! Lou decides to run against him with a sloth named Mrs. Fuzzybelly.

episodes.name: Snow Cups and Fisticuffs
episodes.overview: To help the campers stay cool during a heat wave, Lou announces that she’s finally caved and bought a shaved ice machine for Camp Kikiwaka.

episodes.name: The S'more, The S'merrier
episodes.overview: With the end of summer on the horizon, Destiny reminds Finn and Matteo that they need to hang as much as possible with the time they have left.

episodes.name: Lava at First Sight
episodes.overview: When Ava’s brother Alex visits Camp Kikiwaka, Lou develops a crush on him!

episodes.name: Town and Clown Relations
episodes.overview: Lou puts on a fundraiser carnival at the camp to raise money for her first cause as Deputy Mayor.

episodes.name: Whisper Toots
episodes.overview: When Noah and Destiny notice Matteo sneaking off into the woods at night, they follow him and soon discover he is moonlighting at Miss Tilly's Inn.

episodes.name: My Fairy Lady
episodes.overview: Finn is not pleased when he finds out his mother's boyfriend, Dave, is coming to visit Camp Kikiwaka.

episodes.name: Party Pooper
episodes.overview: Lou is invited to a conference for camp directors, where she has been asked to give a speech; she allows Destiny to come with her, but soon regrets that decision.

episodes.name: Squatters’ Fights
episodes.overview: When Ava, Destiny and Gwen discover that the Grizzly cabin has a much larger bathroom than theirs, they hatch a diabolical plan to convince the boys to switch cabins.

episodes.name: Three Stars and a Baby
episodes.overview: When Lou asks the campers to fill out counselor evaluations, Ava fears Destiny and Gwen’s ratings and worries that her job may be in jeopardy.

episodes.name: Manic Moose Day
episodes.overview: When Lou’s travel-blogger friend, Sean, visits camp, Lou hopes it will help drive some business. But Lou quickly realizes it may be harder to impress her than expected.

episodes.name: Breaking Barb
episodes.overview: The Southern Northeast Conference of Camp Directors encourages Lou and Barb to participate in a camp director swap program.

episodes.name: Raven About Bunk’d
episodes.overview: Raven, Chelsea, Booker, Nia, Levi, and Tess set out on a long road trip to Maine's Camp Champion, but a GPS glitch sends them off course to Camp Kikiwaka, a place with an uncertain future even for those who can catch a glimpse of the future.

4.name: Season 4
4.overview: After purchasing Camp Kikiwaka—for one dollar—from the Ross siblings, the always cheerful Lou is adjusting to her new duties as camp director with her usual brand of over-the-top enthusiasm. She’s thrilled to be reunited with campers Destiny, Finn and Matteo, who have returned for another exciting summer full of fun and friendship. Lou also welcomes some new faces, including camp counselor Noah, an upbeat and enthusiastic actor from Hollywood; Ava, a tenacious counselor from the big city; and Gwen, an eccentric new camper who has spent her entire life living off the grid.

episodes.name: Lou's Still the Boss, But Now There's a Ross
episodes.overview: Camp director Lou, counselors Ava and Noah and campers Destiny, Matteo and Finn are delighted when Emma, fresh from her glamorous career as a fashion designer in Milan, pays a surprise visit to Camp Kikiwaka.

episodes.name: Rise of the Machine
episodes.overview: Noah and Ava face a new challenge when they take over the "PeeWeeWaka" day camp program for younger campers. Meanwhile, Destiny and Finn express very different styles when they co-host the camp radio news show.

episodes.name: R.V. Having Fun Yet?
episodes.overview: Much to Lou's surprise, Parker Preston arrives at Camp Kikiwaka to stake his claim to part ownership of the camp.

episodes.name: Tentacle Difficulties
episodes.overview: Ava volunteers Noah for a field trip to the Moose Rump Aquarium, but it turns out Noah's terrified of the ocean's creatures. Parker and Destiny debate the importance of a majestic tree.

episodes.name: Luck of the Chuck
episodes.overview: Ava and Noah work together to put on a puppet show for the PeeWeeWaka campers while Destiny helps Lou prepare for an important camp inspection.

episodes.name: Look Who's Squawking
episodes.overview: Ava insists that she wants to take on more responsibility this summer, so Lou assigns her the task of resurrecting the "Camper of the Week" program.

episodes.name: Raucous Science
episodes.overview: Lou signs up for a chemistry class to finish her college degree and is surprised to discover that Matteo is her professor. Meanwhile, Finn learns he has a new little sister on the way.

episodes.name: Baton-man Begins
episodes.overview: While visiting Finn in the hospital, Noah develops a crush on Destiny's new friend. Meanwhile, Ava attempts to interest Finn in reading.

episodes.name: Everyone's Trap'd
episodes.overview: With Lou stressed about camp duties, Parker completes Lou's assignment and drops it off at Matteo's classroom, but Lou does not want Matteo to think she cheated.

episodes.name: Pop Pop Poppin' In
episodes.overview: Hoping to be discovered, Noah enlists a reality TV crew. Lou’s overbearing grandfather pays a visit and criticizes her camp-running abilities.

episodes.name: Roll Models
episodes.overview: Ava and Destiny compete in an elaborate marble race. Lou, Matteo and Noah head off on a road trip where they encounter Noah’s NASA-bound older brother.

episodes.name: Gi Whiz
episodes.overview: Finn and Destiny look for a way to leave their mark on the camp. While meeting Matteo’s mother, Lou and Noah discover that he has a surprising skill.

episodes.name: Dancin' Up a Storm
episodes.overview: Lou drops in on her cousins at their family farm only to receive an icy reception to her surprise visit. Parker tries some creative methods to teach Finn how to dance.

episodes.name: Out of the Doghouse
episodes.overview: Destiny is excited for Ava to become an official Woodchuck. However, Lou tells Destiny that the initiation is canceled due to the noise complaints Junkyard Judy keeps filing against the camp.

episodes.name: The Great Awkward Bake-Off
episodes.overview: Lou sets up a cookie gram, where campers can send messages on cookies. Ava volunteers to run the project with Dante, and Destiny suspects it's because Ava has a crush on him.

episodes.name: I Won't Let You Clown
episodes.overview: Destiny re-discovers the clowning life when her friend Claire pays a visit; Lou enlists Parker and Noah to compete in a contest against Barb.

episodes.name: Crushin' It
episodes.overview: When Gwen returns for a surprise visit to camp, Noah and Destiny hatch a plan to create dangerous situations for Gwen to fix, hoping it will compel her to stay.

episodes.name: Camp Creepy-Waka
episodes.overview: When issues arise between her campers, Lou’s “Scary Story Night” helps them work through their differences.

episodes.name: A Star is Torn
episodes.overview: Lou’s favorite actress, Melody Chapman, comes to camp to shadow Lou as research for an acting role.

episodes.name: Moose Queens and Possum Kings
episodes.overview: When Destiny needs someone old enough to enter the Summer Moose Queen pageant, she enlists Parker and Ava for help.

episodes.name: Frien'ds Forever
episodes.overview: As another fun summer at Camp Kikiwaka comes to an end, the campers must confront change and fear of the unknown.

5.name: Season 5
5.overview: Back for another exciting summer at the sometimes struggling Camp Kikiwaka in rural Maine are the enthusiastic camp owner/director Lou, counselors Ava and Noah, and returning campers Destiny, Matteo and Finn, who are all ready to tackle new and hilarious adventures.

episodes.name: Learning the Ropes
episodes.overview: Lou and Parker must convince The Marshal to sell them the ranch. Noah and Destiny clash with new campers Bill, Jake, and Winnie.

episodes.name: Never a Dull Moo-ment
episodes.overview: Parker discovers something about the ranch's history. Destiny struggles with her first assignment as a counselor. Noah gets curious about what Bill does in his free time.

episodes.name: Worst Aid
episodes.overview: Winnie plans a risky stunt, to secretly audition for a reality stunt show, with Bill and Jake's help. Lou and Noah teach first aid to Destiny and Parker, but Destiny struggles under the pressure.

episodes.name: Wrecks Mark Spot
episodes.overview: Bill searches for treasure with Destiny's reluctant help, despite Lou's disapproval; Parker and Noah plan a dance performance but struggle to include Jake.

episodes.name: Truth Sweat Free
episodes.overview: Noah gets a mascot job downtown for The Marshal's unsavory new business. Parker asks Lou and Bill to teach him how to be a rancher. Destiny gets hooked on Jake's video games.

episodes.name: Where the Buffalo Betties Roam
episodes.overview: Lou, Bill and Destiny must get the jade compass back from a group of haughty socialites. Parker tries to improve the ranch with Winnie's help. Jake and Noah get a new roommate.

episodes.name: A Recipe for Disaster
episodes.overview: A child genius asks Parker and Bill to help her learn to have fun, while Destiny gets Winnie a drum set as an outlet for her energy. Lou and Jake set out to revitalize the food.

episodes.name: Back in the Saddle
episodes.overview: With Lou's help, Destiny competes in the Dusty Tush Rodeo Pageant. Parker, Winnie and Jake build a parade float, and Bill and Noah get an announcing job at the rodeo.

episodes.name: Bunkhouse of Horror
episodes.overview: A mysterious handyman tells the camp three spooky stories set on the ranch involving a cursed bracelet, a possessed scarecrow and a magic wishing well.

episodes.name: Hauntin’ Around the Christmas Tree
episodes.overview: Parker learns some important lessons about Christmas.

episodes.name: Hope You Geyser Ready to Go!
episodes.overview: Lou wants a group picture in front of an active geyser that only erupts every fifteen years, so Parker must get everyone up and ready so they can make it there in time.

episodes.name: The Song Remains A Pain
episodes.overview: Lou wins an award from a magazine, but Bill is suspicious of the reporter's motives. Parker and Jake prep Noah for a date. Destiny and Winnie try to write a song for their cabin.

episodes.name: Art Imitates Life
episodes.overview: Jake displays an unusual talent, which reveals secrets around the camp. Winnie is eager to ride a horse, and Bill tries to cover up a mistake.

episodes.name: Wild West Side Story
episodes.overview: A new dance camp has started nearby, which presents different challenges to Lou and Parker. Bill and Noah go fishing, and Winnie struggles with sleep deprivation.

episodes.name: The Wrath of Con
episodes.overview: A local convention featuring Noah's movie is disrupted by an unexpected star. Meanwhile, The Marshal's niece comes to camp, and Jake thinks he's discovered something in the lake.

episodes.name: Finn It To Win It
episodes.overview: Finn visits Kikiwaka Ranch on a mission, Bill’s new pet causes problems, and Winnie tries to fix a lock with disastrous results.

episodes.name: Alpaca-lypse Now
episodes.overview: Destiny, Bill and Parker must stall a livestock auction to retrieve a clue in the treasure hunt, Jake works on a gift for his moms, and Noah practices stunts.

episodes.name: The Wicked Switch of the West
episodes.overview: When Winnie becomes counselor for a day, Destiny decides to show her how her reckless behavior affects others. Meanwhile, Noah receives some bad news, and Lou plans a livestream.

episodes.name: No Pain, No Grain
episodes.overview: Winnie helps her brother Wayne propose to his boyfriend during their visit to the camp. Lou and Destiny teach Bill about self-care, and Parker finally gets his own place to stay.

episodes.name: Shoe Drops and Chili Plops
episodes.overview: Noah and Parker compete to win a pair of designer shoes. Bill enters a chili competition. Lou finds an old landline phone in the mess hall.

episodes.name: Pickett Fencing
episodes.overview: Bill’s twin sister Jill visits, ruining his hopes for a low-key birthday. Destiny and Jake suspect that Lou found the Lost Treasure of Dusty Tush. Noah teaches Winnie to fence.

episodes.name: Model Citizen
episodes.overview: Parker is nervous about his citizenship test. Destiny asks Jake to model her new clothing line. Noah takes Bill to the local ice cream shop, and Bill struggles to pick a flavor.

episodes.name: Camp Fails and Beaver Tails
episodes.overview: Unsupervised for the day, Winnie, Bill and Jake canoe to an island in the middle of Lake Tush. Parker wants to create a new camp activity. Lou helps Noah build a bookcase.

episodes.name: Tap'd Out
episodes.overview: Lou gets invited to join a Dusty Tush secret society; Jake is upset as he does not feel strong, so Noah and Bill make it seem like he's stronger; Winnie learns to dance.

episodes.name: Badminton to the Bone
episodes.overview: Destiny, Bill and Winnie get trapped in a bank vault while treasure hunting; Jake helps Lou and Parker find common ground; Noah finds out Megan has an ultra-competitive side.

episodes.name: For Letter or Worse
episodes.overview: Destiny plans the Tush Heritage Festival; Lou, Bill, and Jake resort to old school transportation methods to pick up BBQ; Parker tells Victoria how he feels.

episodes.name: Butter You Doing Here?
episodes.overview: Noah and Destiny must work with Ken, "The Perfect Counselor." Jake tells Winnie that she's one of his best friends. Bill enters a Future Ranchers of Dusty Tush competition.

episodes.name: Writer's Locked
episodes.overview: Lou invites her biggest fan, Oliver, to the camp to read her latest book. Noah gets invited to attend the premiere of his first movie. Parker asks Bill and Jake to watch his dog.

episodes.name: Most Wanted
episodes.overview: Winnie is accused of causing a stampede. Noah asks Parker and Megan to help him choose his next acting role. Bill gets "Most Changed" in his camp yearbook and spirals.

episodes.name: Desperate Treasures
episodes.overview: Desperate to save the ranch, Winnie, Bill, and Jake decide to finish the hunt for the Dusty Tush treasure. Meanwhile, Lou, Parker, and our counselors decide to hold a telethon.

6.name: Leaning the Ropes
6.overview: Lou, Parker, Destiny and Noah arrive at the soon-to-be Kikiwaka Ranch in Dusty Tush, Wyoming, where Lou must convince the surly owner, a.k.a. "The Marshal" to officially sell the property to her. In the meantime, counselors Noah and Destiny have their hands full with the newly arrived campers, including Bill, a no-nonsense descendant of famous cowboy Bill Pickett who prefers roping cattle to hanging out with friends; Winnie, a fearless girl who's earned the nickname "Wild Winnie" by breaking the rules and occasionally blowing things up; and Jake, a laid-back, easy-going boy who also happens to be a video-gaming fanatic.

episodes.name: Cursed Day of Camp
episodes.overview: Parker, Bill and Jake try to convince a reluctant Lou that the camp is cursed; Winnie and Destiny help a new camper fit in

episodes.name: Workaversary Girl
episodes.overview: Noah bonds with a new camper over their love for puppets; Lou enlists Winnie to help her pull a surprise together for Parker on their "Workaversary."

episodes.name: Meat Cute
episodes.overview: Destiny and Parker compete to open a restaurant on Main Street; Winnie enlists Noah to help her sleep without her baby blanket.

episodes.name: An Arrow Victory
episodes.overview: After a food critic arrives at Destiny's restaurant, things quickly go awry; Parker tricks Winnie into thinking she's good at archery to boost her self-esteem.

episodes.name: Hot Couture
episodes.overview: Winnie, Bill, Jake and Scout compete for A/C on the hottest day of the summer while Destiny and Noah compete to prove they are the best dressed counselor at camp.

episodes.name: What About Barb?
episodes.overview: Lou, Winnie and Jake team up to help Barb Barca.

episodes.name: Don't Hate the Mayor, Hate the Game

7.name: Leaning the Ropes
7.overview: The hijinks continue at Kikiwaka Ranch with Lou, her right-hand man Parker, plus counselors Destiny and Noah along for the ride. Cowboy Bill, daredevil Winnie and gamer Jake are also back for another summer full of excitement and new adventures.
